üü¢ Topic ‚û° Switch-Case Control Instructions (Java Version)

Write a Java program that takes the month number as input and displays the number of days in that month using switch-case.

Write a menu-driven Java program with the following options using switch-case:
a. Addition
b. Subtraction
c. Multiplication
d. Division
e. Exit

Write a Java program that takes the day number of the week as input and displays a unique greeting message for each day using switch-case.

Write a menu-driven Java program with the following options using switch-case:
a. Check whether the given set of three numbers can form an isosceles triangle
b. Check whether the given set of three numbers can form a right-angled triangle
c. Check whether the given set of three numbers can form an equilateral triangle
d. Exit

Convert the following if-else-if construct into a Java switch-case statement:


if(var == 1)
    System.out.println("good");
else if(var == 2)
    System.out.println("better");
else if(var == 3)
    System.out.println("best");
else
    System.out.println("invalid");
Write a Java program to check whether a year is a leap year or not using a switch-case statement.

Write a Java program to calculate the total electricity bill based on the number of units entered by the user using switch-case.

For the first 50 units: Rs. 0.50/unit

For the next 100 units: Rs. 0.75/unit

For the next 100 units: Rs. 1.20/unit

For units above 250: Rs. 1.50/unit

Add a 20% surcharge to the final bill

Write a Java program to convert a positive number into a negative number and vice versa using switch-case.

Write a Java program to convert an even number to its immediate upper nearest odd number using switch-case.

Write a Java program to find all roots of a quadratic equation using switch-case.







